Package aa.test.selenium

Class AA02CreateProjectTest

java.lang.Object
aa.test.utils.AASeleniumManager
aa.test.selenium.AA02CreateProjectTest
@TestMethodOrder(org.junit.jupiter.api.MethodOrderer.DisplayName.class) class AA02CreateProjectTest extends AASeleniumManager
 Tests for creating projects.
 
 We currently test creating projects with new and existing names and project
 types with new and existing names. We are creating the project types from
 Create project modal (three scenarios does, one does not create the project
 type at all).
 
 Date field - always set to 26th of the next month.
 
 Are the projecs billable? We are currently testing:
 - all project types are created non-billable
 - all projects are created billable with fixed fee
 
 We are asserting that the client-snackbar says either that the new project
 was created, or that the project name already exists (analogically with the
 project types).
 
 If tests run on DEV, STAGING, or PROD, all the projects already exists. If
 it's running in Docker, some tests create new projects.
